# Add Phone Number Registration with SMS OTP

Add a toggle on the registration form allowing users to register via **Email** or **Phone Number**. Phone registration sends a real SMS OTP using **Twilio**.

**Updated flow:** Register (Email or Phone) → OTP Verify → CAPTCHA → MFA Setup

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> To send real SMS messages, you'll need a **Twilio account** (free trial available at [twilio.com](https://www.twilio.com)).
> You'll need to provide: `TWILIO_ACCOUNT_SID`, `TWILIO_AUTH_TOKEN`, and `TWILIO_PHONE_NUMBER` in your [.env](file:///home/usan/home/mystuff/usan/mfa-2/.env).
> Twilio free trial lets you send SMS to verified phone numbers only.

## Proposed Changes

### Dependencies
- Install `twilio` npm package for SMS delivery.

### Backend
#### [MODIFY] [server.js](file:///home/usan/home/mystuff/usan/mfa-2/server.js)
- Add Twilio client initialization using env vars.
- Modify `POST /api/register` to accept an optional `phone` field and a `method` field (`email` or `phone`).
  - If `method === 'phone'`: send OTP via Twilio SMS instead of email.
  - If `method === 'email'`: existing email flow (unchanged).
- Store `method` in `pendingUsers` so `/api/verify-email` knows which method was used.

#### [MODIFY] [.env](file:///home/usan/home/mystuff/usan/mfa-2/.env) and [.env.example](file:///home/usan/home/mystuff/usan/mfa-2/.env.example)
- Add `TWILIO_ACCOUNT_SID`, `TWILIO_AUTH_TOKEN`, `TWILIO_PHONE_NUMBER`.

### Frontend
#### [MODIFY] [index.html](file:///home/usan/home/mystuff/usan/mfa-2/public/index.html)
- Add a toggle (two buttons/tabs) on the registration form: "Register with Email" / "Register with Phone".
- Show email input or phone input based on selection.

#### [MODIFY] [app.js](file:///home/usan/home/mystuff/usan/mfa-2/public/js/app.js)
- Track which registration method is selected (`email` or `phone`).
- Send the correct `method` and `phone`/`email` field to `/api/register`.

## Verification Plan
- Test email registration (unchanged behavior).
- Test phone registration with a valid Twilio-verified number.
- Verify OTP → CAPTCHA → MFA flow works for both methods.
